  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "41\n6\n\nhence theodicy? I might wind up with a universe I understood which was devoid of theodicy - in which case we would have built-in tragedy facing us!) (Viz: theoretically it might bipolarize this way: 1) Would you prefer to be destroyed + understand why (by \"destroyed\" read \"doomed\")? 2) Or would you prefer to be saved + not understand why (by \"saved\" read \"given joy + life\" - by \"life\" read einai)? We have been mislead by Hellenestic thought- + Attic Greece gave rise to classical tragic dra",
      "matched_alias": "Judo",
